Excellent B movie ,no plot but lots of action and cool cars. Reminded me of the junks I used to drive all jacked op with shackles and air shocks. Ahh the good ol' days of bias ply 60 series tires, massive smokey burn outs and street racing at every light. If you grew up in the 70's it's a must watch brought back some good memories.

A perfect film to watch and critique the filmmakers technique. Lessons to be learned about shot transition, takes, camera placement, shot angles, and footage sequencing. Even more points to be learned on scriptwriting, acting, delivery, and how to climax and end a film. Overall it was an entertaining way to passively experience a film and enjoy related discussion during the screening.
